spacing(x) returns the absolute spacing of model numbers near x.

default real examples:
x = -10  spacing(x) = 9.536743e-07
x = -1  spacing(x) = 1.192093e-07
x = -0.5  spacing(x) = 5.960464e-08
x = 0  spacing(x) = 1.175494e-38
x = 0.5  spacing(x) = 5.960464e-08
x = 1  spacing(x) = 1.192093e-07
x = 10  spacing(x) = 9.536743e-07

kind examples:
spacing(1.0)   = 1.192093e-07
spacing(1.0_4) = 1.192093e-07
spacing(1.0_8) = 2.22044604925031e-16

nearby-value examples:
spacing(1.0)              = 1.192093e-07
spacing(nearest(1.0,1.0)) = 1.192093e-07
spacing(2.0)              = 2.384186e-07

spacing(0.0) is the spacing near zero:
spacing(0.0) = 1.175494e-38
tiny(0.0)    = 1.175494e-38
